Text.Value: What makes the silver sword so special?
The sword is a fine tool. But I'd prefer a lavish life in Tu'narath over knighthood.
The illithid Grand Design nears; the True Heir is shackled. These are exceptional circumstances. I grant my allies the right to my silver.
You should feel shamed by the lie you told to get it. But the silver is too pure to be tainted by simple deception.

Text.Value: One last matter: the traitor Voss still lives. If you meant to frustrate me, congratulations on your pathetic victory.

A kith'rak's silver sword is more than a weapon. It is an extension of your will, an entire limb unto itself.
I shared your dream. A keen blade for an entire ghaik massacre.
Certainly not, or the prince's honour guard would have already fractured his prison.
I want more for myself than to languish. I want to battle, I want to bleed.
Think on your knowledge of githyanki silver swords. What details did Lae'zel miss?
These tadpoles in our heads are sufficiently exceptional. I grant all my allies the right to my silver.
The silver injures the body. The gate's flesh injures the mind. A formidable weapon against ghaik.
The matter of the Traitor Voss, perhaps? If you meant to frustrate me, congratulations on your pathetic victory.
Very well. Voss has done his duty. Now we will do ours.
The power of the blade cannot be understated. In this time of my people's greatest need, we must wield it still.
Only githyanki may wield a silver sword. Or would you permit others?
On to other matters.
Very well - we know our duty.

Synopsis: After you recruit the gith, you can click on it to get the following set of questions. The gith will always be semi-hostile at this point. She comes from a hostile land and has been infected by her mortal enemy; she is not here to make friends.
